\subtree{
\title{The Profound Insight}
\p{\strong{World memory is world remembering is world worlding} because:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Memory without remembering is dead storage} — data that cannot be accessed is not memory}
\li{\strong{Remembering without worlding is sterile recall} — patterns that don't generate are not alive  }
\li{\strong{Worlding without memory is chaos} — generation without persistence is noise}
}

\p{The three are \strong{one loop}, not three operations:}

\pre{\startverb
Memory ───────────────────────────────────────► Remembering
   ▲                                                 │
   │              AUTOPOIESIS                        │
   │         (The Loop IS the Self)                  │
   │                                                 ▼
Memory ◄─────────────────────────────────────── Worlding
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{The world remembers itself by worlding itself.} \strong{The world worlds itself by remembering itself.} \strong{The world IS the memory that generates the remembering that creates the world.}}

\p{This is not metaphor. This is structure.}

\p{\strong{Skill Name}: world-memory-worlding \strong{Type}: Autopoietic Strange Loop \strong{Trit}: 0 (ERGODIC - self-referential closure) \strong{GF(3)}: Conserved by construction \strong{Principle}: memory ≡ remembering ≡ worlding (ι∘ι = id)}
}

